1
00:00:10,867 --> 00:00:13,167
<i>Are you ready
for your next move?</i>

2
00:00:13,300 --> 00:00:14,967
<i>You're dead! This is impossible!</i>

3
00:00:15,100 --> 00:00:16,433
<i> Because you killed me.</i>

4
00:00:16,567 --> 00:00:17,400
<i> No!</i>

5
00:00:17,533 --> 00:00:19,200
<i>Leave me alone!
You're already dead!</i>

6
00:00:19,333 --> 00:00:20,267
<i> Auntie Jade!</i>

7
00:00:20,400 --> 00:00:22,500
<i>Jade, can you please stop
pranking Mookie?</i>

8
00:00:22,633 --> 00:00:23,767
<i> She's getting scared.</i>

9
00:00:23,900 --> 00:00:27,900
<i>Syndicates and criminals
use Necrosol</i>

10
00:00:28,033 --> 00:00:30,733
<i>to make their victims fall
asleep instantly.</i>

11
00:00:30,867 --> 00:00:32,333
<i> Hi, Sis. Did you miss me?</i>

12
00:00:32,467 --> 00:00:34,167
<i> You're not real.</i>

13
00:00:34,333 --> 00:00:35,767
<i> Go on and try.</i>

14
00:00:35,900 --> 00:00:36,867
<i> Go ahead!</i>

15
00:00:39,833 --> 00:00:40,767
<i>- Zayn!
- What's your problem?</i>

16
00:00:40,900 --> 00:00:42,533
<i>Did Stacy tell you to do that?
Answer me!</i>

17
00:00:42,667 --> 00:00:42,933
<i> Yes.</i>

18
00:00:43,067 --> 00:00:44,133
<i> Stacy!</i>

19
00:00:44,267 --> 00:00:46,100
<i>You'll regret it if you hurt
my girlfriend again.</i>

20
00:00:47,433 --> 00:00:49,467
<i>How will you use
that to scare her?</i>

21
00:00:49,600 --> 00:00:51,600
<i> Go ahead and scream!</i>

22
00:00:51,733 --> 00:00:54,567
<i> No one will hear you.</i>

23
00:01:37,300 --> 00:01:38,200
Please stop.

24
00:01:38,333 --> 00:01:39,633
- What?
- Stop.

25
00:01:39,767 --> 00:01:41,000
Stop?

26
00:01:43,133 --> 00:01:44,100
Why?

27
00:01:44,233 --> 00:01:45,767
Why?

28
00:01:45,900 --> 00:01:48,367
Does it hurt your ears?

29
00:01:48,500 --> 00:01:50,700
How does it feel?

30
00:01:50,833 --> 00:01:52,667
Does it feel like
you're being tortured?

31
00:01:54,567 --> 00:01:55,800
Is it deafening?

32
00:01:56,933 --> 00:01:58,267
Please stop.

33
00:01:58,400 --> 00:02:01,000
That's what Emma does
to me right now.

34
00:02:04,700 --> 00:02:06,733
Here in my ear.

35
00:02:06,867 --> 00:02:09,167
She laughs so loud!

36
00:02:10,333 --> 00:02:12,767
She's haunting me!

37
00:02:12,900 --> 00:02:14,567
Emma's haunting you?

38
00:02:16,367 --> 00:02:17,300
Maybe...

39
00:02:19,067 --> 00:02:21,367
Maybe you deserve to be haunted

40
00:02:21,500 --> 00:02:23,867
because of all the things you
did to her.

41
00:02:24,000 --> 00:02:29,033
And maybe Jade must haunt you
as well.

42
00:02:29,167 --> 00:02:30,500
Shut up!

43
00:02:33,700 --> 00:02:34,700
You talk too much!

44
00:03:00,867 --> 00:03:02,567
Where is it coming from?

45
00:03:02,700 --> 00:03:04,200
Do you hear that?

46
00:03:09,633 --> 00:03:10,900
Where is it coming from?

47
00:03:12,333 --> 00:03:12,933
What's that?

48
00:03:14,467 --> 00:03:17,000
Where is it coming from?
Answer me!

49
00:03:17,133 --> 00:03:18,867
You're working with Emma,
aren't you?

50
00:03:19,000 --> 00:03:20,267
Are you in cahoots with her?

51
00:03:20,400 --> 00:03:22,467
Tell me the truth!

52
00:03:22,633 --> 00:03:24,633
Is Emma haunting you again?

53
00:03:27,967 --> 00:03:29,633
What are you talking about?

54
00:03:29,767 --> 00:03:31,133
How can I do that?

55
00:03:32,333 --> 00:03:33,900
You killed Emma.

56
00:03:34,033 --> 00:03:36,733
You locked me up here.
You chained me!

57
00:03:37,967 --> 00:03:40,733
How is that even possible?

58
00:03:40,867 --> 00:03:44,167
I wish I could work with her in
the afterlife.

59
00:03:44,300 --> 00:03:46,133
So we could stop your evilness.

60
00:03:48,200 --> 00:03:50,633
Do you miss them?

61
00:03:50,767 --> 00:03:53,333
Do you miss Emma and Jade?

62
00:03:54,867 --> 00:03:57,900
Do you want to reunite with them
in the grave?

63
00:03:58,033 --> 00:03:59,833
Are you going to kill me, too?

64
00:03:59,967 --> 00:04:02,000
That would be better.

65
00:04:02,133 --> 00:04:04,233
I'd rather be with my children

66
00:04:04,367 --> 00:04:08,167
than be in this hell
of a place with you.

67
00:04:16,467 --> 00:04:17,967
Where is it coming from?

68
00:04:26,433 --> 00:04:34,467
No!

69
00:04:45,367 --> 00:04:47,667
Dr. Samson has already replied.

70
00:04:47,800 --> 00:04:48,667
What did she say?

71
00:04:51,200 --> 00:04:52,733
Sorry.

72
00:04:52,867 --> 00:04:56,833
It's like I've been zapped.

73
00:04:56,967 --> 00:04:57,833
Sorry.

74
00:04:57,967 --> 00:04:58,800
What...

75
00:04:58,933 --> 00:05:00,033
I'll read it.

76
00:05:02,433 --> 00:05:03,467
Okay.

77
00:05:03,600 --> 00:05:10,900
Pryvaxil is a maintenance drug
for hallucinations.

78
00:05:11,033 --> 00:05:12,233
No!

79
00:05:12,367 --> 00:05:13,333
No!

80
00:05:13,467 --> 00:05:14,667
No!

81
00:05:14,800 --> 00:05:17,067
No!

82
00:05:32,033 --> 00:05:34,700
I've had enough.

83
00:05:41,667 --> 00:05:45,933
Jade already has a mental health
condition.

84
00:05:47,367 --> 00:05:50,100
She's now having hallucinations.

85
00:05:50,233 --> 00:05:53,833
She's been hearing and seeing
all sorts of things.

86
00:05:56,700 --> 00:06:02,600
You mean Jade also has a mental
health condition like Olive.

87
00:06:02,733 --> 00:06:04,000
Exactly.

88
00:06:06,233 --> 00:06:08,533
So, keep haunting her.

89
00:06:10,167 --> 00:06:12,033
We'll drive her even more crazy.

90
00:06:30,567 --> 00:06:32,700
Stop!

91
00:06:32,833 --> 00:06:35,633
I don't want to hear
that kind of song!

92
00:06:38,333 --> 00:06:40,167
Why, dear?

93
00:06:43,167 --> 00:06:50,033
I remember my child,
Maria Angela.

94
00:06:53,133 --> 00:06:55,833
She came into my life

95
00:06:55,967 --> 00:07:00,033
when all the people I loved
left me.

96
00:07:03,867 --> 00:07:06,500
She was my perfect baby.

97
00:07:11,933 --> 00:07:14,200
No!

98
00:07:14,367 --> 00:07:20,000
When she died,
my heart died with her.

99
00:07:24,133 --> 00:07:26,567
Why did she have to die?

100
00:07:26,700 --> 00:07:31,100
Why not me?

101
00:07:31,233 --> 00:07:34,633
I wish I had died
instead of her.

102
00:07:34,767 --> 00:07:38,300
Maria Angela, my child.

103
00:07:40,067 --> 00:07:40,933
I'm sorry, dear.

104
00:07:43,067 --> 00:07:44,133
Please forgive me.

105
00:07:44,267 --> 00:07:49,000
Because I wasn't there
by your side to comfort you.

106
00:07:50,600 --> 00:07:53,733
It could have made you
feel better.

107
00:07:55,300 --> 00:07:57,767
But I'm here now, dear.

108
00:07:57,900 --> 00:07:59,567
Your mom is here.

109
00:07:59,700 --> 00:08:01,533
I will fill the void

110
00:08:01,667 --> 00:08:05,500
that Maria Angela had left
in your heart.

111
00:08:05,633 --> 00:08:07,200
I will love you.

112
00:08:07,333 --> 00:08:09,800
I will never leave you.

113
00:08:09,933 --> 00:08:12,033
I will love you with all
my heart.

114
00:08:12,167 --> 00:08:13,667
I promise you that.

115
00:08:13,800 --> 00:08:15,533
Liar!

116
00:08:15,667 --> 00:08:18,400
- You're a liar!
- I will love you.

117
00:08:18,533 --> 00:08:22,300
I will never leave you, dear.
I'm not lying to you.

118
00:08:22,467 --> 00:08:23,933
I don't believe you.

119
00:08:24,067 --> 00:08:25,167
Shut up!

120
00:08:28,000 --> 00:08:35,367
You are a cold-hearted monster
pretending to be a mother.

121
00:08:37,433 --> 00:08:40,167
You've insulted me way too much.

122
00:08:41,600 --> 00:08:42,600
How about you?

123
00:08:44,333 --> 00:08:46,733
Do you know how to love?

124
00:08:46,867 --> 00:08:48,600
You're worse than me!

125
00:08:50,367 --> 00:08:55,600
Because a person who loves also
knows how to forgive.

126
00:08:55,767 --> 00:08:59,200
You don't know that word.

127
00:08:59,333 --> 00:09:01,500
It's not in your vocabulary.

128
00:09:01,633 --> 00:09:02,600
Shut up!

129
00:09:02,733 --> 00:09:04,533
All you know is to get angry
at me and blame me

130
00:09:04,667 --> 00:09:07,767
for all the pain you had!

131
00:09:07,900 --> 00:09:09,367
Shut up!

132
00:09:09,500 --> 00:09:11,000
Yes,

133
00:09:11,133 --> 00:09:15,667
I may be the reason for all the
hatred you have in your heart.

134
00:09:15,800 --> 00:09:16,700
Shut up!

135
00:09:16,833 --> 00:09:21,567
But remember that it's you
who nurtured it!

136
00:09:21,700 --> 00:09:22,800
Shut up!

137
00:09:22,933 --> 00:09:24,800
- You made it grow!
- Shut up!

138
00:09:24,933 --> 00:09:27,433
I'm not the cruel one. It's you!

139
00:09:27,600 --> 00:09:31,533
You stole someone's daughter!
You stole someone's husband!

140
00:09:31,667 --> 00:09:34,167
- You killed your own sisters!
- Shut up!

141
00:09:34,300 --> 00:09:35,967
You're the cruel one!

142
00:09:36,100 --> 00:09:37,167
Not me!

143
00:09:37,300 --> 00:09:38,400
Shut up!

144
00:09:45,100 --> 00:09:46,533
I don't want it anymore.

145
00:09:46,667 --> 00:09:48,267
Stop.

146
00:09:56,433 --> 00:10:00,200
It says here that Pryvaxil
treats hallucinations.

147
00:10:00,333 --> 00:10:01,433
Yes.

148
00:10:01,600 --> 00:10:04,833
Then Jade can counter
what I do to her.

149
00:10:04,967 --> 00:10:06,367
You know what, Emma?

150
00:10:06,500 --> 00:10:11,900
In a battle, there's something
called disarmament.

151
00:10:12,033 --> 00:10:17,333
You target the opponent's weapon
first before you attack.

152
00:10:19,933 --> 00:10:21,733
We'll get it.

153
00:10:21,867 --> 00:10:23,067
How? Steal it?

154
00:10:24,800 --> 00:10:25,933
I'm thinking of something else.

155
00:10:27,400 --> 00:10:29,400
Maybe it's better

156
00:10:29,533 --> 00:10:31,767
if we will replace the contents
of the bottle.

157
00:10:31,900 --> 00:10:35,967
That way, we can trigger her
hallucinations even more.

158
00:10:38,767 --> 00:10:40,000
I like that.

159
00:10:44,933 --> 00:10:49,933
Stop.

160
00:10:50,067 --> 00:10:51,967
I don't want it anymore.

161
00:11:03,500 --> 00:11:07,600
What we're doing to Jade
is getting worse and worse.

162
00:11:07,767 --> 00:11:08,700
Yeah.

163
00:11:08,833 --> 00:11:14,067
But the challenge is how
are we going to do that?

164
00:11:15,933 --> 00:11:17,767
Leave it to me.

165
00:11:17,900 --> 00:11:20,133
I already have someone in mind.

166
00:11:22,267 --> 00:11:25,800
I can use her to do that task.

167
00:11:36,067 --> 00:11:38,533
Mister, please give me one.

168
00:11:38,667 --> 00:11:39,700
Bro,

169
00:11:39,833 --> 00:11:43,433
why didn't she introduce or show
herself if she was Emma?

170
00:11:43,600 --> 00:11:45,667
And you danced with her.
How come you didn't notice it?

171
00:11:45,800 --> 00:11:47,933
I did.

172
00:11:48,067 --> 00:11:50,900
I just can't see her face fully
because it's dark.

173
00:11:51,033 --> 00:11:53,800
And she's hiding her face so
that I wouldn't recognize it.

174
00:11:53,933 --> 00:11:55,567
You should stop, bro.

175
00:11:55,700 --> 00:11:56,500
That wasn't Emma.

176
00:11:56,633 --> 00:11:58,767
No, I have a strong feeling
about it.

177
00:11:58,900 --> 00:12:00,500
That was Emma.

178
00:12:00,633 --> 00:12:03,100
Let's say it was Emma.

179
00:12:03,233 --> 00:12:04,967
But why didn't she introduce
herself?

180
00:12:05,100 --> 00:12:06,833
That's what I'm wondering, too.

181
00:12:06,967 --> 00:12:08,667
Maybe she wanted to say
something,

182
00:12:08,800 --> 00:12:10,567
but someone was stopping her.

183
00:12:12,400 --> 00:12:14,067
That's possible.

184
00:12:14,200 --> 00:12:17,600
Can you help me?

185
00:12:17,767 --> 00:12:18,733
You know someone who works

186
00:12:18,867 --> 00:12:20,867
for the Road and Transportation
Authority, right?

187
00:12:21,000 --> 00:12:24,167
Can we ask them for help?

188
00:12:24,300 --> 00:12:26,367
I really want to see Emma.

189
00:12:26,967 --> 00:12:27,767
Okay.

190
00:12:30,900 --> 00:12:33,767
Please put it on my tab.
I'll pay for it.

191
00:12:33,900 --> 00:12:37,100
Here, eat first.
This is where I work part-time.

192
00:12:37,233 --> 00:12:38,100
Thank you.

193
00:12:38,233 --> 00:12:39,333
Tell me everything that's
happened to you.

194
00:12:39,467 --> 00:12:40,733
How are you?

195
00:12:40,867 --> 00:12:42,967
We haven't seen each other
for a while.

196
00:12:43,100 --> 00:12:43,867
I've missed you.

197
00:12:45,333 --> 00:12:47,800
What happened to you
at Havenwood?

198
00:12:47,967 --> 00:12:49,267
That was unbelievable.

199
00:12:49,400 --> 00:12:51,367
I went there to see you.

200
00:12:51,500 --> 00:12:53,800
Manang Sefa works there.

201
00:12:53,933 --> 00:12:55,167
She told me you were there.

202
00:12:55,300 --> 00:12:57,700
But when I got there,
you were gone.

203
00:12:57,833 --> 00:13:00,333
Where did you go when you left
Havenwood?

204
00:13:00,467 --> 00:13:02,967
And why didn't you show up
sooner?

205
00:13:03,100 --> 00:13:05,267
And why do you look so beautiful
now?

206
00:13:05,400 --> 00:13:06,900
You look different.

207
00:13:07,033 --> 00:13:07,900
Wait.

208
00:13:08,033 --> 00:13:09,367
Have you met with Mookie
and Danilo already?

209
00:13:09,500 --> 00:13:10,367
Hold on.

210
00:13:10,500 --> 00:13:11,933
Hold on, Flor.
You ask so many questions.

211
00:13:12,067 --> 00:13:14,433
I will answer them.

212
00:13:14,567 --> 00:13:18,033
But for now, my husband
and child can't see me.

213
00:13:18,167 --> 00:13:19,500
Why?

214
00:13:19,633 --> 00:13:21,700
Jade drove me crazy.

215
00:13:21,867 --> 00:13:25,033
Danilo and Mookie no longer
believe me.

216
00:13:25,167 --> 00:13:28,200
Jade told them I went with
another man.

217
00:13:28,333 --> 00:13:31,700
I don't know what happened.

218
00:13:31,833 --> 00:13:36,633
But I can't understand why he
replaced me with another woman.

219
00:13:36,767 --> 00:13:40,733
If he really loves me,
we will never replace me.

220
00:13:40,867 --> 00:13:42,533
I knew it.

221
00:13:42,667 --> 00:13:44,900
Jade really is a monster.

222
00:13:45,033 --> 00:13:47,333
She takes after her older
sister, Olive.

223
00:13:48,933 --> 00:13:53,000
Flor, I need your help
to get even with Jade.

224
00:13:53,133 --> 00:13:56,433
Please tell me how I can help.
Go!

225
00:13:56,600 --> 00:13:59,400
Can you apply for a housekeeping
job at Jade's house?

226
00:13:59,533 --> 00:14:02,200
You'll keep an eye on her
and replace her medicine.

227
00:14:02,333 --> 00:14:06,433
You mean you'll drive her crazy
like she did to you?

228
00:14:06,567 --> 00:14:07,567
Yes, Flor.

229
00:14:09,533 --> 00:14:11,967
Game!

230
00:14:12,100 --> 00:14:15,133
But we have a problem.

231
00:14:15,267 --> 00:14:20,333
Kutsy and Wiro told me that Jade
already has a house help.

232
00:14:20,467 --> 00:14:22,800
But not a stay-in.
What do we do about that?

233
00:14:22,933 --> 00:14:24,800
That's Loida.

234
00:14:24,933 --> 00:14:27,133
I'll take care of her.

235
00:14:27,267 --> 00:14:28,400
Nice.

236
00:14:28,567 --> 00:14:32,967
Then, when will we enter
the vulture's nest?

237
00:14:33,100 --> 00:14:35,533
As soon as possible.

238
00:14:35,667 --> 00:14:39,733
It's better to disturb
the monster when it's not ready.

239
00:14:39,867 --> 00:14:44,067
And if she's ready,
I won't back down.

240
00:15:09,867 --> 00:15:11,967
Sir Danilo, you have a visitor.

241
00:15:12,100 --> 00:15:14,967
- Let him in, Loida.
- Okay, Sir.

242
00:15:22,733 --> 00:15:23,700
- Bro!
- Bukoy!

243
00:15:23,833 --> 00:15:25,633
- What's the update?
- Danilo.

244
00:15:25,767 --> 00:15:27,267
I have news for you.

245
00:15:27,400 --> 00:15:29,333
I already know who owns the car.

246
00:15:31,233 --> 00:15:32,567
Am I going to see Emma?

247
00:15:32,700 --> 00:15:34,300
Wait.

248
00:15:34,433 --> 00:15:35,433
Calm down.

249
00:15:35,600 --> 00:15:36,667
We're not sure about it yet.

250
00:15:36,800 --> 00:15:40,600
And even if you see Emma,
what will you do?

251
00:15:40,733 --> 00:15:41,500
Will you get back together
with her?

252
00:15:41,633 --> 00:15:42,167
How about Jade?

253
00:15:43,700 --> 00:15:44,433
You're right.

254
00:15:44,567 --> 00:15:45,900
But no.

255
00:15:46,033 --> 00:15:48,100
I'll think about that later,
Bukoy.

256
00:15:48,233 --> 00:15:50,133
What matters is to meet
with Emma.

257
00:15:50,267 --> 00:15:52,033
So I will know what really
happened to her.

258
00:15:53,600 --> 00:15:55,800
But do you know who
the car owner is?

259
00:15:55,933 --> 00:15:57,200
Do you know his name?

260
00:15:57,333 --> 00:15:58,800
Yes. Wait.

261
00:15:58,933 --> 00:16:02,300
I got his license.

262
00:16:02,433 --> 00:16:04,167
Here. He is Marco Delos Reyes.

263
00:16:04,300 --> 00:16:06,067
My friend gave me that.

264
00:16:10,567 --> 00:16:11,000
<i> Sir?</i>

265
00:16:11,133 --> 00:16:11,733
<i> What is it, bro?</i>

266
00:16:12,433 --> 00:16:14,033
<i> I'm looking for a woman.</i>

267
00:16:14,167 --> 00:16:15,933
<i> Did you see anyone?</i>

268
00:16:16,067 --> 00:16:16,767
<i> No.</i>

269
00:16:16,900 --> 00:16:18,233
I remember him.

270
00:16:18,367 --> 00:16:20,867
<i> Danilo, she's gone forever!</i>

271
00:16:21,000 --> 00:16:23,267
<i> She left you for another man.</i>

272
00:16:23,400 --> 00:16:24,533
<i> She loves someone else now.</i>

273
00:16:24,667 --> 00:16:25,733
<i> And that's not you!</i>

274
00:16:27,233 --> 00:16:28,833
<i> Emma is gone.</i>

275
00:16:28,967 --> 00:16:31,000
<i> She's gone forever!</i>

276
00:16:32,467 --> 00:16:35,967
Don't you think this
is Emma's lover?

277
00:16:53,567 --> 00:16:56,600
Zintrixa-X or ZX.

278
00:16:56,733 --> 00:16:58,933
That's what we're going to
replace the tablets with.

279
00:16:59,067 --> 00:17:01,767
Jade's Pryvaxil.

280
00:17:01,900 --> 00:17:06,967
It will cause her hot temper,
irritability,

281
00:17:07,100 --> 00:17:12,200
anger, paranoia, and,
the best part, hallucinations.

282
00:17:14,267 --> 00:17:17,433
In short, it'll drive her crazy.

283
00:17:17,600 --> 00:17:20,900
Let Jade chug it so she'll
completely go insane.

284
00:17:22,200 --> 00:17:24,300
I didn't know your friend
was funny.

285
00:17:24,433 --> 00:17:25,100
Okay.

286
00:17:25,233 --> 00:17:26,733
I'll leave you two for now.

287
00:17:26,867 --> 00:17:27,800
Marco.

288
00:17:29,733 --> 00:17:32,400
By the way, Emma.

289
00:17:32,533 --> 00:17:35,300
I told the kitchen
to cook food for you.

290
00:17:35,433 --> 00:17:36,567
It's for the two of you.

291
00:17:36,700 --> 00:17:39,767
I'll have Flor eat it.
I've already eaten.

292
00:17:39,900 --> 00:17:42,667
Are you referring to the pizza
slice you ate earlier?

293
00:17:44,433 --> 00:17:50,367
10 grams of fat, 35 grams
of carbs, 12.2 grams of protein.

294
00:17:50,533 --> 00:17:52,533
You think that will get you
through the day?

295
00:17:52,667 --> 00:17:54,567
I don't think so, Emma.

296
00:17:54,700 --> 00:17:56,367
Eat what they've cooked for you.

297
00:17:56,500 --> 00:17:58,333
There's fish, veggies, and meat.

298
00:17:59,800 --> 00:18:00,367
Thank you.

299
00:18:05,033 --> 00:18:07,800
I can easily replace Jade's
medicines with this.

300
00:18:07,933 --> 00:18:08,933
You know me.

301
00:18:11,000 --> 00:18:12,033
So, are you ready?

302
00:18:12,167 --> 00:18:13,800
Are you ready for your mission?

303
00:18:13,933 --> 00:18:15,133
Of course!

304
00:18:24,833 --> 00:18:27,000
Bro, bro! Here's the car.

305
00:18:27,133 --> 00:18:28,133
Here's the house.

306
00:18:31,467 --> 00:18:32,533
Anybody home?

307
00:18:32,667 --> 00:18:35,233
<i>Make sure you have a valid
excuse, Emma.</i>

308
00:18:35,367 --> 00:18:38,500
<i>I don't understand why you're
playing with me like this.</i>

309
00:18:53,467 --> 00:18:54,300
Hello?

310
00:18:55,533 --> 00:18:56,567
Anybody home?

311
00:19:03,200 --> 00:19:05,733
Bro, bro. Wait. Hold on.

312
00:19:05,867 --> 00:19:07,200
I know you.

313
00:19:07,333 --> 00:19:09,000
Do you own this car?

314
00:19:09,133 --> 00:19:09,833
Yes.

315
00:19:09,967 --> 00:19:10,767
Why?

316
00:19:10,900 --> 00:19:11,767
Where's Emma?

317
00:19:11,900 --> 00:19:12,833
Emma?

318
00:19:12,967 --> 00:19:13,867
Emma who?

319
00:19:15,967 --> 00:19:17,700
Darn you! You're the one spying
at our house, aren't you?

320
00:19:17,833 --> 00:19:19,200
Bro, calm down!

321
00:19:19,333 --> 00:19:20,500
- Hey!
- It was you!

322
00:19:27,300 --> 00:19:28,133
Bring my wife out!

323
00:19:28,300 --> 00:19:29,667
You fool!

324
00:19:29,800 --> 00:19:31,633
Do you want me to blow
your jaw off?

325
00:19:31,767 --> 00:19:33,567
- Are you threatening me?
- You, too!

326
00:19:33,700 --> 00:19:35,400
- You again?
- Bring my wife out!

327
00:19:42,033 --> 00:19:43,533
You know me?

328
00:19:43,667 --> 00:19:45,267
Of course.

329
00:19:45,400 --> 00:19:47,500
I won't forget you.

330
00:19:47,633 --> 00:19:49,600
I just danced with you
at the event,

331
00:19:49,733 --> 00:19:51,467
and you told me your life story.

332
00:20:10,400 --> 00:20:12,500
You're not the woman
I danced with.

333
00:20:12,633 --> 00:20:14,467
Why do you insist that?

334
00:20:14,600 --> 00:20:16,867
Do you want me to tell you
everything we talked about

335
00:20:17,000 --> 00:20:17,833
that night?

336
00:20:17,967 --> 00:20:20,067
About Emma?

337
00:20:20,200 --> 00:20:21,233
Darn it!

338
00:20:21,367 --> 00:20:23,367
Is he the crazy man you're
telling me about?

339
00:20:23,500 --> 00:20:25,333
The one who insisted
that you're his wife?

340
00:20:25,467 --> 00:20:26,567
Yes, brother.

341
00:20:26,700 --> 00:20:28,733
But I saw her outside the hotel.

342
00:20:28,867 --> 00:20:30,400
She was the one I danced with.

343
00:20:30,533 --> 00:20:31,733
I know.

344
00:20:31,867 --> 00:20:33,567
You chased me, right?

345
00:20:38,567 --> 00:20:40,100
<i> Emma, I know it's you.</i>

346
00:20:42,100 --> 00:20:43,800
<i>Aren't you planning to be with
Mookie again?</i>

347
00:20:44,733 --> 00:20:45,633
Fine.

348
00:20:46,500 --> 00:20:47,633
If that's really you?

349
00:20:47,767 --> 00:20:48,933
What did I tell you to stop you

350
00:20:49,067 --> 00:20:51,367
from running if it was really
you?

351
00:20:53,400 --> 00:20:54,500
What?

352
00:20:54,633 --> 00:20:56,567
Why can't you answer?

353
00:20:58,200 --> 00:20:58,967
Hello?

354
00:20:59,100 --> 00:21:00,633
Police station?

355
00:21:00,767 --> 00:21:03,100
A pervert is harassing
my sister.

356
00:21:05,600 --> 00:21:06,800
Come here now.

357
00:21:06,933 --> 00:21:08,033
That's enough. Let's go.

358
00:21:08,200 --> 00:21:09,833
They're lying.

359
00:21:09,967 --> 00:21:11,000
That's enough! Come on!

360
00:21:12,833 --> 00:21:13,533
Let's go.

361
00:21:15,700 --> 00:21:17,600
- Don't ever come back!
- She's lying!

362
00:21:26,533 --> 00:21:27,900
Ma'am, would you like
a banana cue?

363
00:21:28,033 --> 00:21:28,900
It's only 20 pesos.

364
00:21:35,300 --> 00:21:36,667
- Flor?
- Flor!

365
00:21:36,800 --> 00:21:38,733
- Mookie! Zayn!
- Flor!

366
00:21:38,867 --> 00:21:41,800
I missed you! How are you?

367
00:21:41,967 --> 00:21:43,033
How are you?

368
00:21:43,167 --> 00:21:44,733
It's been a long time since
we last saw each other.

369
00:21:44,867 --> 00:21:47,067
I'm still jobless.

370
00:21:47,200 --> 00:21:48,833
My contract has just ended.

371
00:21:48,967 --> 00:21:52,433
So I'm selling for
a living for now.

372
00:21:52,567 --> 00:21:57,067
Mookie, I'll be shameless.

373
00:21:57,200 --> 00:21:59,733
Do you know any regular job?

374
00:22:01,200 --> 00:22:02,600
Maybe I can work at your house!

375
00:22:02,733 --> 00:22:03,833
I can be your house help again.

376
00:22:03,967 --> 00:22:05,400
Please?

377
00:22:05,533 --> 00:22:07,333
Okay.

378
00:22:07,467 --> 00:22:09,867
I'll talk to Aunt Jade
when I get home.

379
00:22:10,000 --> 00:22:10,700
Really?

380
00:22:10,833 --> 00:22:11,867
Thank you, Mookie.

381
00:22:12,000 --> 00:22:13,333
Thank you so much.

382
00:22:14,700 --> 00:22:15,567
Please get my number.

383
00:22:15,733 --> 00:22:16,367
Sure, Flor.

384
00:22:16,500 --> 00:22:17,267
Text me.

385
00:22:17,400 --> 00:22:18,433
And please buy some from me.

386
00:22:18,567 --> 00:22:21,300
I got you, Flor.

387
00:22:21,433 --> 00:22:23,300
Mommy Olive is gone.

388
00:22:23,433 --> 00:22:28,233
So, I'm sure I can convince Aunt
Jade to let you stay with us.

389
00:22:28,367 --> 00:22:30,133
Thank you.

390
00:22:30,267 --> 00:22:33,167
Here's my number. Save it.
And please text me.

391
00:22:33,300 --> 00:22:33,733
There.

392
00:22:33,867 --> 00:22:35,800
0957...

393
00:22:38,300 --> 00:22:40,233
Save it, please.

394
00:22:40,367 --> 00:22:41,200
This only costs 20 pesos.

395
00:22:41,333 --> 00:22:42,100
We'll get two.

396
00:22:42,233 --> 00:22:44,367
Thank you.
I'll just get a change.

397
00:22:44,500 --> 00:22:44,967
It's okay.

398
00:22:45,100 --> 00:22:46,400
What? Are you sure?

399
00:22:46,533 --> 00:22:48,400
Thank you!

400
00:22:48,567 --> 00:22:50,233
You're my first buyer.
Thank you.

401
00:22:50,367 --> 00:22:51,200
- Bye, Flor.
- Text me, okay?

402
00:22:51,333 --> 00:22:52,367
Yes, I'll text you.

403
00:22:52,500 --> 00:22:53,533
Thank you.

404
00:22:53,667 --> 00:22:55,300
You're so kind.

405
00:22:55,433 --> 00:22:56,733
Thank you!

406
00:22:59,933 --> 00:23:00,833
She's not the woman
I danced with!

407
00:23:01,833 --> 00:23:03,000
It was Emma!

408
00:23:04,200 --> 00:23:05,700
Bro! That's enough!

409
00:23:07,667 --> 00:23:09,267
It wasn't her! It was Emma!

410
00:23:11,167 --> 00:23:12,400
Stop!

411
00:23:14,900 --> 00:23:16,000
What do I do?

412
00:23:19,533 --> 00:23:21,367
I'm sorry, bro.

413
00:23:21,500 --> 00:23:23,300
I'm so confused.

414
00:23:25,400 --> 00:23:26,600
Emma's bothering me.

415
00:23:27,833 --> 00:23:29,300
I can't take her off my mind.

416
00:23:30,700 --> 00:23:32,933
I see her even in my dreams.

417
00:23:33,067 --> 00:23:35,100
Why doesn't she tell me
what the problem is?

418
00:23:36,367 --> 00:23:38,767
Why doesn't she say if
she'll come back to me?

419
00:23:40,567 --> 00:23:42,600
Why did she have to leave
me and her daughter?

420
00:23:44,300 --> 00:23:46,267
Doesn't she care for Mookie?

421
00:23:52,800 --> 00:23:54,433
My daughter's alone.

422
00:23:56,800 --> 00:23:58,600
Her mom isn't with her.

423
00:23:58,733 --> 00:23:59,900
She left us.

424
00:24:01,200 --> 00:24:03,667
Doesn't she feel bad
for her child?

425
00:24:03,800 --> 00:24:05,733
She's making us suffer.

426
00:24:14,367 --> 00:24:15,467
Hey.

427
00:24:15,600 --> 00:24:17,567
What's with the long face?

428
00:24:17,700 --> 00:24:18,900
Everything's good now.

429
00:24:19,933 --> 00:24:22,500
Your plan worked.
Mookie will help me.

430
00:24:23,600 --> 00:24:25,033
I feel guilty.

431
00:24:25,167 --> 00:24:27,333
I'm using Mookie too.

432
00:24:27,467 --> 00:24:29,433
Come on, Emma.
Stop being dramatic.

433
00:24:29,600 --> 00:24:33,633
She's the only way to get inside
Jade's house, remember?

434
00:24:35,100 --> 00:24:36,700
And it's all for Mookie.

435
00:24:38,800 --> 00:24:39,833
You're right.

436
00:24:40,267 --> 00:24:41,500
It's for Mookie.

437
00:24:41,633 --> 00:24:43,333
I want to get even with Jade.

438
00:24:44,367 --> 00:24:45,300
And more than that...

439
00:24:46,833 --> 00:24:48,767
I want to take back
what she stole from me.

440
00:24:50,000 --> 00:24:51,733
I am Mookie's only mother.

441
00:24:51,867 --> 00:24:54,333
Not Olive and Jade.

442
00:24:54,467 --> 00:24:59,033
Those demons can't be Mookie's
mother.

443
00:25:09,100 --> 00:25:10,867
I'm sorry, Ma'am Jade.

444
00:25:11,000 --> 00:25:14,233
I received a job offer
with a higher pay.

445
00:25:14,367 --> 00:25:16,467
No, you can't do that.

446
00:25:16,600 --> 00:25:18,700
Loida, you can't resign.

447
00:25:18,833 --> 00:25:20,467
Thank you, Loida.

448
00:25:20,600 --> 00:25:23,933
You're a big help in getting
Mookie back from Jade.

449
00:25:24,067 --> 00:25:28,333
Flor needs a job, Auntie.

450
00:25:28,467 --> 00:25:29,833
There.

451
00:25:29,967 --> 00:25:31,100
Your problem is solved.

452
00:25:31,233 --> 00:25:34,467
I'll observe for now
so I can get updated.

453
00:25:36,333 --> 00:25:37,600
Gotcha!

454
00:25:39,367 --> 00:25:39,933
Emma?

455
00:25:40,067 --> 00:25:41,000
Next.

456
00:25:41,133 --> 00:25:43,300
Are you ready?

457
00:25:43,433 --> 00:25:44,900
What's happening to you? Ligaya!

458
00:25:45,033 --> 00:25:45,700
Hey!

459
00:25:45,833 --> 00:25:46,800
No!

460
00:25:46,933 --> 00:25:48,167
No!

461
00:25:48,300 --> 00:25:50,233
You can't die!

462
00:25:50,367 --> 00:25:53,167
You can't die on me!
I won't allow you!

463
00:25:53,300 --> 00:25:55,867
Hello, Leticia? Come with me.

464
00:25:56,000 --> 00:25:58,100
Let's meet at San Bartolome
Community Hospital.

465
00:25:58,233 --> 00:25:59,133
Now.

466
00:26:00,700 --> 00:26:01,767
Hello Emma?
